This is a 2009 build Rossi 92 in .44 Mag. 20" Octagon Barrel, Case hardened reciever. It has both the large loop and the small loop lever for it. I have polished all internals and the action is very smooth. It has a reduced power ejector spring so cases fall at your feet, not in the next county. Bolt safety removed and plug installed. title: For Sale:  Mossberg 500 Chainsaw
postcontent: Certainly one of the most unusual-looking guns to come out is the Mossberg 500 Chainsaw. Built in the iconic Mossberg 500 action, the Chainsaw is a pistol-grip pump-action shotgun with no stock. While guns like this are desirable for home defense, they're notoriously hard to control while firing, a problem that Mossberg has solved by attaching a wrap-around chainsaw-style hand grip to the pump. Intended to be fired from the hip, this top handle allows the user to cycle the action while simultaneously maintaining leverage above the gun to help tame muzzle flip. In addition to the chainsaw-style grip, the 500 Chainsaw has a stand-off barrel that can be used to breech doors and three rails that can mount accessories.
